----- Original Message ----- 
From: "Karl von Salzen" <aufever(-at-)hotmail.com>
-------------------------------------------------------
>
> I ran the Redline MT90 in my 77 Westy. I had a problem when it got hot.
> It expanded and ran out the input shaft and left big puddles. No, it was
not
> overfull. The input shaft is higher than the fill plug. Cold, it was to
the
> level of the fill plug; where it is supposed to be. Drove the bus and when
it
> got hot and started dripping from the clutch area, I removed the fill plug
and
> about a pint poured out!  Drained out the MT90 and went back to Sta-Lube
GL-4
> and never had a problem again.
